<h2 class="bac">Our Business:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Global Commercial Banking (GCB) is the leading commercial bank in the U.S., serving one out of three companies with revenues of between $2.5 million and several billion dollars.  GCB generates more than $10 billion in annual revenue and $4 billion in net income from a variety of market-leading capital raising and treasury businesses. It serves more than 155,000 corporate clients through dedicated client teams who provide seamless, integrated delivery of the bank&#39;s full capabilities. GCB associates offer clients unrivaled market access, flexibility and value through our core businesses.
</p>
<p class="bac">
Global Product Solutions (GPS) designs, delivers and services integrated credit and treasury products to more than 140,000 clients around the world, including small businesses, middle-market and large corporations, multi-nationals, financial institutions and governments. These solutions, distributed through client managers, include business and corporate lending, global payments and liquidity management, commercial card services, trade finance, foreign exchange, lines of credit and equipment finance solutions. GPS is the number one treasury services provider in the United States and a leading provider globally, serving 95 percent of U.S. Fortune 500 companies and 73 percent of the Global Fortune 500.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Overview:</h2>  
<p class="bac">
The program is designed to build strong talent for client-facing roles in Global Commercial Banking and Global Product Solutions. The program emphasizes on-the-job training augmented by classroom instruction focused on technical, analytical and professional skills. Functional areas include treasury management, financial modeling and credit analysis, risk fundamentals and relationship management. 
</p>
<p class="bac">
Program analysts complete six-month rotations to provide broad exposure and understanding of key functional areas. Rotations provide exposure to credit and treasury with intensive focus on how to best deliver innovative solutions to our clients. Designated program analysts will participate in Commercial Real Estate training during the credit rotations. As a member of the Analyst Program, you will have exposure to members of the leadership team and the opportunity to interact with our clients. Rotations are completed in the same city. 
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Qualifications:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Candidates must have a bachelor&#39;s degree with a minimum of six (6) credit hours of finance and/or accounting. Candidates must have a demonstrated record of achievement, such as extracurricular activities or leadership roles. Some common driving characteristics include: finance knowledge, excellent verbal and written communication skills, personal leadership, the ability to inspire a strong sense of camaraderie and technical skills such as Excel and PowerPoint.  
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Training:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Virtual, web-based and instructor-led learning solutions are used to supplement the experiential development that occurs on-the-job. Throughout the program, analysts are provided a support network, which consists of the program manager, rotation managers and mentors. An important part of this network is former college program analysts.
</p>

<img src="../images/clear.gif" class="bac" alt=""><br clear="all">

<h2 class="bac">Locations:</h2>
<p class="bac">
Positions are available in major markets across the Bank&nbsp;of&nbsp;America footprint. Line-of-business and location assignment is based on business need and candidate interest. Geographic flexibility is required at the end of the program in an effort to fill business-critical roles.
</p>

